<div id="careers">

    <div class="sectionTextCenterJob">
        <p>
            <span class="sectionTextHeadlineCareer">Graphic Designer</span>
    </div>

    <div class="sectionTextJob">
        <p>
			We are currently seeking a versatile in-house Graphic Designer who can wear a lot of different hats. 
			We're looking for someone who is just as happy working on in-house graphics needs that come up as 
			they are assisting our development teams with their web application graphics needs for our clients. 
			Experience developing web applications from the front end is a huge plus, so please highlight and 
			send any examples of programming you've done in languages/frameworks such as Java, JavaScript, jQuery, Angular.js, etc.
        </p>

        <p>
            <span class="careerHeadline">Responsibilities:</span><br>
        </p>
        <ul id="jobList">
			<li>Support teams by creating all artwork for software applications as well as non-software requests.</li> 
			<li>Work closely with Development teams to translate business requirements into detailed user experience designs.</li>
			<li>Design all print media, collateral production for sales and marketing, and web site assets.</li>
			<li>Design within brand guidelines or established look and feel while delivering original, innovative and strategically sound creative solutions.</li> 
			<li>Follow art direction and process artistic and technical feedback in a professional manner.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            <span class="careerHeadline">We want to work with you if:</span><br>
        </p>
        <ul id="jobList">
            <li>You can manage & prioritize your design projects, working either independently or with a team.</li>
            <li>You are ego-free, remain open to change, and can design to suit the needs of our team and our clients.</li>
            <li>You are a smart, creative, proactive problem solver. </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            <span class="careerHeadline">Requirements:</span><br>
        </p>
        <ul id="jobList">
			<li>Bachelor's Degree in Graphic Design (or equivalent experience).</li>
			<li>Mastery of Adobe Creative Suite, especially Photoshop, InDesign & Illustrator.</li> 
			<li>Proficiency in HTML, CSS, Java, JavaScript, jQuery, Angular.js is highly desired.</li>
			<li>Demonstrated understanding of marketing and communications strategies.</li>
			<li>Proven knowledge of visual design principles, including graphic design, layout, typography, color and branding.</li>
			<li>Experience in web site design, updates and mobile web.</li>
			<li>Ability to work under deadline pressure.</li>
			<li>A great team attitude and the desire to work with a small group of your peers, without hierarchy or politics.</li>

        </ul>
    </div>

    <div id="careerFooterText">
		<p>To apply, please e-mail your cover letter and resume to <a href="mailto:join@altsrc.net">join@altsrc.net</a>. 
		To learn more about us, please visit our web site at <a href="../index.html" rel="nofollow">www.altsrc.net</a> or Facebook page at 
		<a href="https://www.facebook.com/AltSource" rel="nofollow">www.facebook.com/AltSource</a>.
		</p>	
	</div>
